If the game just exit do desktop when you try to start it, it's because of your refresh rate. It's the exact same problem that BF1942 had... Quote: "- Battlefield 1942 has that annoying refresh rate crap where every time you patch it you have to go into the config file and change the "allow all refresh rates" from 0 to 1 so the game works if you use a refresh rate other than 60 Hz." Where "patch" = fresh install in this case Anyways you find the config file in modsbf2settings and it's called VideoDefault.con (just open with notepad) and the line is renderer.allowAllRefreshRates If there's a Video.con file in that folder too you might wanna copy the line into that config and set it to 1 as well. Just in case anyone encounters this problem... Thanks to a user for this info! ;-)

I finally figured out how to fix that damn crash to desktop error when using a GF4TI card.

1) download the Microsoft Framework from 
http://www.microsoft.com/downloads/details.aspx?FamilyId=262D25E3-F589-4842-8157-034D1E7CF3A3&displaylang=en
and install it.

2) download DXTweaker: http://mrbauer.net/files/dxtweaker.rar

3) Extract to a folder on desktop

4) Run DXTweaker, and goto "New" on the right

5) Point it to your root BF2 EXE (in your EA Sportsbattlefield 2 DIR)

6) Check the 2 boxes that contain 'SHADER' , one is FORCE SHADER FP and the other is FORCE SHADER PP.

7) Click Apply, and then click RUN on the top.

It will launch the game with no problems and you will be playing very smoothly.

Why is there graphical corruption in the game? 

  Question 
  Why is there graphical corruption in the game?


  Answer 
  Graphical corruption is usually a conflict with the video card or other display settings in the system.

Verify that your video card meets all system requirements, and it is using the newest manufacturer video drivers.
Click here for steps on verifying requirements and driver versions.
Adjust your desktop resolution to 1024x768 for the best compatibility with your game.
Click here for steps on changing your desktop resolution.
If you have raised any video/graphics settings in the game from their defaults, lower them back to their default setting

Why does the game crash to the desktop after a full black screen? 
 ==============================
  Question 
  Why does the game crash to the desktop after a full black screen?
  ==============================

  Answer 
  This issue is typically caused by a conflict with the video card or video card drivers.  Make sure your video card meets the requirements for the game, and that your drivers are the newest version available from the manufacturer.
 ==============================
The supported video cards are as listed below:
 ==============================
ATI Radeon
 ==============================
X700 (PCIe), X600 (PCIe), X800 XT Platinum Edition, X800 PRO, X300 series.
9800 series, 9700 series, 9600 series, 9559 (RV350LX), 9500 series, 8500 series.
NVIDIA GeForce
 ==============================
6600 (PCIe), PCX 5900 (PCIe).
5800 series (AGP).
6800 Ultra, 6800 GT, 6800.
FX 5950 series, FX 5900 series, FX 5700 series.
 ==============================
If you are not using one of these video card chipsets, the game may run improperly or may not run at all.  The game was tested to communicate properly with the aforementioned chipsets using the newest drivers.  If you have one of these cards but are still experiencing the issue, it is likely that the drivers you have are not the newest manufacturer version.
 ==============================

Note that if you have a ATI Radeon 9200 PCI card (this does not apply to AGP or PCI Express cards), you may experience this issue even after updating your drivers.  Although this card meets the memory requirements for running the game, when tested it was not able to run the game with a stability adequate enough to make the official supported video card list in the Readme for the game.  Updating your video card drivers as well as your motherboard firmware may help to resolve this issue.  Please refer to your video card manufacturer for further instruction.
 ==============================
